The **Urease Test** is an important biochemical test used to determine the ability of microorganisms to produce the enzyme **urease**. This enzyme hydrolyzes **urea** into **ammonia (NH₃)** and **carbon dioxide (CO₂)**, which increases the pH of the medium and changes the color of the indicator. It is widely used in differentiating members of the family *Enterobacteriaceae* and in identifying certain pathogens such as *Helicobacter pylori*.
